main details to prepare kraken/bakta db images:

(1.)
ami to build from:
=> Amazon ECS-Optimized Amazon Linux 2023
===> then look for: (AL2023) x86_64 AMI

(2.)
=> instance type:
r5.4xlarge

(3.)
ebs root storage:
 size:250 GB
 IOPS: 16000
 Throughput: 1000

 (4.)
 check ecs agent:
 $ sudo systemctl status ecs

 (5.)
 create db dir:
 sudo mkdir -p /opt/databases
 mount volume with db kraken/bakta

(6.)
sudo rsync -ahW --inplace --info=progress2 /mnt/sdb/ /opt/databases/

(7.)
System cleanup:

# Ensure Docker starts on boot
sudo systemctl enable docker

# Stop ECS agent
sudo systemctl stop ecs

# Clean ECS state
sudo rm -rf /var/lib/ecs/data/*

sudo systemctl enable ecs

